WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.820 --> 00:00:14.820
I know what you're thinking.
我知道你们在想什么。

2
00:00:14.820 --> 00:00:16.820
You think I've lost my way,
你们想我迷路了，

3
00:00:16.820 --> 00:00:18.820
and somebody's going to come on the stage in a minute
有人马上会上台

4
00:00:18.820 --> 00:00:20.820
and guide me gently back to my seat.
把我领回到我的座位。

5
00:00:20.820 --> 00:00:26.820
(Applause)
(掌声)

6
00:00:26.820 --> 00:00:29.820
I get that all the time in Dubai.
在迪拜老是有人这样问我。

7
00:00:29.820 --> 00:00:31.820
"Here on holiday are you, dear?"
“亲爱的，来度假啊？”

8
00:00:31.820 --> 00:00:33.820
(Laughter)
(笑声)

9
00:00:33.820 --> 00:00:36.820
"Come to visit the children?
“来看孩子们吗？

10
00:00:36.820 --> 00:00:38.820
How long are you staying?"
呆多久啊？”

11
00:00:38.820 --> 00:00:41.820
Well actually, I hope for a while longer yet.
事实上，我希望我还能多在这儿呆几年呢。

12
00:00:41.820 --> 00:00:44.820
I have been living and teaching in the Gulf
我在海湾地区已经生活和教书

13
00:00:44.820 --> 00:00:46.820
for over 30 years.
有30多年了。

14
00:00:46.820 --> 00:00:50.820
(Applause)
(掌声)

15
00:00:50.820 --> 00:00:54.820
And in that time, I have seen a lot of changes.
在这期间，我目睹了很多变化。

16
00:00:54.820 --> 00:00:56.820
Now that statistic
那些统计数据

17
00:00:56.820 --> 00:00:58.820
is quite shocking.
是令人非常吃惊的。

18
00:00:58.820 --> 00:01:00.820
And I want to talk to you today
而我今天要跟你们讲的

19
00:01:00.820 --> 00:01:02.820
about language loss
是关于语种的消失

20
00:01:02.820 --> 00:01:05.820
and the globalization of English.
和英语的全球化。

21
00:01:05.820 --> 00:01:07.820
I want to tell you about my friend
我想告诉你们，我的一个朋友

22
00:01:07.820 --> 00:01:10.820
who was teaching English to adults in Abu Dhabi.
她在阿布扎比教成年人英语。

23
00:01:10.820 --> 00:01:12.820
And one fine day,
一天，

24
00:01:12.820 --> 00:01:14.820
she decided to take them into the garden
她决定带他们去花园

25
00:01:14.820 --> 00:01:16.820
to teach them some nature vocabulary.
去教他们一些大自然用语。

26
00:01:16.820 --> 00:01:18.820
But it was she who ended up learning
但是结果她反而学了所有

27
00:01:18.820 --> 00:01:20.820
all the Arabic words for the local plants,
当地植被的阿拉伯名称

28
00:01:20.820 --> 00:01:22.820
as well as their uses --
和它们的用途--

29
00:01:22.820 --> 00:01:25.820
medicinal uses, cosmetics,
药用的，化妆用的，

30
00:01:25.820 --> 00:01:28.820
cooking, herbal.
食用的， 草药。

31
00:01:28.820 --> 00:01:30.820
How did those students get all that knowledge?
那些学生是怎样得到这些知识的呢？

32
00:01:30.820 --> 00:01:32.820
Of course, from their grandparents
当然是从他们的祖父母那里

33
00:01:32.820 --> 00:01:35.820
and even their great-grandparents.
甚至是他们的曾祖父母那里。

34
00:01:35.820 --> 00:01:38.820
It's not necessary to tell you how important it is
本来我没有必要告诉你们能够

35
00:01:38.820 --> 00:01:40.820
to be able to communicate
跨代交流是多么

36
00:01:40.820 --> 00:01:42.820
across generations.
重要。

37
00:01:42.820 --> 00:01:44.820
But sadly, today,
但是，令人惋惜的是， 今天

38
00:01:44.820 --> 00:01:46.820
languages are dying
很多语种正在

39
00:01:46.820 --> 00:01:48.820
at an unprecedented rate.
以空前的速度消失着。

40
00:01:48.820 --> 00:01:51.820
A language dies every 14 days.
每14天就有一种语言消失。

41
00:01:52.820 --> 00:01:54.820
Now, at the same time,
而同时，现在

42
00:01:54.820 --> 00:01:56.820
English is the undisputed global language.
英语又无可争辩地成为全球性语言。

43
00:01:56.820 --> 00:01:58.820
Could there be a connection?
这两者间有联系吗？

44
00:01:58.820 --> 00:02:00.820
Well I don't know.
我不知道。

45
00:02:00.820 --> 00:02:03.820
But I do know that I've seen a lot of changes.
但是我知道我已目睹了很多变化。

46
00:02:03.820 --> 00:02:06.820
When I first came out to the Gulf, I came to Kuwait
当我初到海湾时， 我到了科威特，

47
00:02:06.820 --> 00:02:09.820
in the days when it was still a hardship post.
那个时候那儿还算是一个艰苦地区。

48
00:02:09.820 --> 00:02:11.820
Actually, not that long ago.
其实也就是没多久以前。

49
00:02:11.820 --> 00:02:14.820
That is a little bit too early.
这幅图还更早一点。

50
00:02:14.820 --> 00:02:16.820
But nevertheless,
不去管它，

51
00:02:16.820 --> 00:02:18.820
I was recruited by the British Council,
我被英国文化协会招聘到这里

52
00:02:18.820 --> 00:02:20.820
along with about 25 other teachers.
同时招来的还有其他25个老师。

53
00:02:20.820 --> 00:02:22.820
And we were the first non-Muslims
我们是最早在科威特

54
00:02:22.820 --> 00:02:25.820
to teach in the state schools there in Kuwait.
公立学校教书的非穆斯林。

55
00:02:25.820 --> 00:02:27.820
We were brought to teach English
我们被请来教英语

56
00:02:27.820 --> 00:02:31.820
because the government wanted to modernize the country
因为政府想要发展国家现代化

57
00:02:31.820 --> 00:02:34.820
and to empower the citizens through education.
让公民通过学习提高自己。

58
00:02:34.820 --> 00:02:36.820
And of course, the U.K. benefited
当然， 英国也因此收益于

59
00:02:36.820 --> 00:02:39.820
from some of that lovely oil wealth.
那些让人喜爱的石油财富。

60
00:02:39.820 --> 00:02:41.820
Okay.
好。

61
00:02:41.820 --> 00:02:44.820
Now this is the major change that I've seen --
这是我看见过的主要变化--

62
00:02:44.820 --> 00:02:46.820
how teaching English
英语教学是怎样

63
00:02:46.820 --> 00:02:48.820
has morphed
演变的

64
00:02:48.820 --> 00:02:52.820
from being a mutually beneficial practice
使它从一个互惠的交流方式

65
00:02:52.820 --> 00:02:55.820
to becoming a massive international business that it is today.
变成如今的一个规模巨大的国际交流。

66
00:02:55.820 --> 00:02:59.820
No longer just a foreign language on the school curriculum,
它不再只是学校课程的一门外语课。

67
00:02:59.820 --> 00:03:01.820
and no longer the sole domain
也不再是

68
00:03:01.820 --> 00:03:03.820
of mother England,
英国特有。

69
00:03:03.820 --> 00:03:05.820
it has become a bandwagon
对地球上每个说英语的国家而言

70
00:03:05.820 --> 00:03:08.820
for every English-speaking nation on earth.
说英语已成为潮流。

71
00:03:08.820 --> 00:03:10.820
And why not?
为什么不呢？

72
00:03:10.820 --> 00:03:13.820
After all, the best education --
毕竟，最好的教育--

73
00:03:13.820 --> 00:03:16.820
according to the latest World University Rankings --
根据最新的世界大学排名--

74
00:03:16.820 --> 00:03:18.820
is to be found in the universities
最好的大学总是

75
00:03:18.820 --> 00:03:22.820
of the U.K. and the U.S.
在英国或者美国。

76
00:03:22.820 --> 00:03:26.820
So everybody wants to have an English education, naturally.
自然每个人都想得到英语教育。

77
00:03:26.820 --> 00:03:28.820
But if you're not a native speaker,
如果你的母语不是英语的话，

78
00:03:28.820 --> 00:03:30.820
you have to pass a test.
你要通过一个考试。

79
00:03:30.820 --> 00:03:32.820
Now can it be right
那么仅仅根据

80
00:03:32.820 --> 00:03:34.820
to reject a student
学生的语言能力

81
00:03:34.820 --> 00:03:36.820
on linguistic ability alone?
就拒绝一个学生的做法合适吗？

82
00:03:36.820 --> 00:03:38.820
Perhaps you have a computer scientist
也许你们中一个计算机科学家

83
00:03:38.820 --> 00:03:40.820
who's a genius.
是一个天才。

84
00:03:40.820 --> 00:03:43.820
Would he need the same language as a lawyer, for example?
那例如，他需要有和律师一样的语言能力吗？

85
00:03:43.820 --> 00:03:46.820
Well, I don't think so.
我并不这么认为。

86
00:03:47.820 --> 00:03:50.820
We English teachers reject them all the time.
我们做英语老师的总是否定他们。

87
00:03:50.820 --> 00:03:52.820
We put a stop sign,
我们放置一个禁止通行的标志，

88
00:03:52.820 --> 00:03:54.820
and we stop them in their tracks.
我们在他们的发展轨道上挡住了他们。

89
00:03:54.820 --> 00:03:56.820
They can't pursue their dream any longer,
他们不能继续追寻他们的梦想，

90
00:03:56.820 --> 00:03:59.820
'til they get English.
除非他们掌握了英语。

91
00:04:00.820 --> 00:04:03.820
Now let me put it this way:
现在我这么说吧，

92
00:04:03.820 --> 00:04:07.820
if I met a monolingual Dutch speaker
如果我遇到一个只会说荷兰语的人

93
00:04:07.820 --> 00:04:09.820
who had the cure for cancer,
他能治愈癌症，

94
00:04:09.820 --> 00:04:12.820
would I stop him from entering my British University?
我会阻止他进入英国大学吗？

95
00:04:12.820 --> 00:04:14.820
I don't think so.
我想不可能。

96
00:04:14.820 --> 00:04:17.820
But indeed, that is exactly what we do.
但是事实上，我们正是这样做的。

97
00:04:17.820 --> 00:04:20.820
We English teachers are the gatekeepers.
我们英语老师是把关的。

98
00:04:20.820 --> 00:04:23.820
And you have to satisfy us first
你得先令我们满意

99
00:04:23.820 --> 00:04:26.820
that your English is good enough.
你的英语要足够好。

100
00:04:27.820 --> 00:04:29.820
Now it can be dangerous
这就可能很危险

101
00:04:29.820 --> 00:04:32.820
to give too much power
把很多权力

102
00:04:32.820 --> 00:04:34.820
to a narrow segment of society.
交给了社会的一个窄小的团体。

103
00:04:34.820 --> 00:04:37.820
Maybe the barrier would be too universal.
可能这个造成的障碍影响面就太广了。

104
00:04:37.820 --> 00:04:39.820
Okay.
好吧。

105
00:04:39.820 --> 00:04:42.820
"But," I hear you say,
“但是” 我听见你们说，

106
00:04:42.820 --> 00:04:44.820
"what about the research?
“那科研呢？

107
00:04:44.820 --> 00:04:46.820
It's all in English."
它们都是用的英语。”

108
00:04:46.820 --> 00:04:48.820
So the books are in English,
书是英语的，

109
00:04:48.820 --> 00:04:50.820
the journals are done in English,
研究刊物是英语的，

110
00:04:50.820 --> 00:04:53.820
but that is a self-fulfilling prophecy.
但是这是一个自我实现的假定。

111
00:04:53.820 --> 00:04:55.820
It feeds the English requirement.
它正好符合需要英语的条件。

112
00:04:55.820 --> 00:04:57.820
And so it goes on.
于是它就继续这样发展下去。

113
00:04:57.820 --> 00:05:00.820
I ask you, what happened to translation?
那我问你，翻译还需要吗？

114
00:05:00.820 --> 00:05:04.820
If you think about the Islamic Golden Age,
如果你想想伊斯兰的黄金时代，

115
00:05:04.820 --> 00:05:07.820
there was lots of translation then.
当时有很多翻译。

116
00:05:07.820 --> 00:05:10.820
They translated from Latin and Greek
他们把拉丁文和希腊语

117
00:05:10.820 --> 00:05:12.820
into Arabic, into Persian,
翻译成阿拉伯语和波斯语，

118
00:05:12.820 --> 00:05:14.820
and then it was translated on
然后又翻译成

119
00:05:14.820 --> 00:05:16.820
into the Germanic languages of Europe
欧洲的日耳曼语

120
00:05:16.820 --> 00:05:18.820
and the Romance languages.
和罗曼语。

121
00:05:18.820 --> 00:05:22.820
And so light shone upon the Dark Ages of Europe.
于是欧洲黑暗的时代被点亮了。

122
00:05:23.820 --> 00:05:25.820
Now don't get me wrong;
不要误会；

123
00:05:25.820 --> 00:05:27.820
I am not against teaching English,
我不是反对教英语，

124
00:05:27.820 --> 00:05:29.820
all you English teachers out there.
或是你们在座的所有英语老师。

125
00:05:29.820 --> 00:05:31.820
I love it that we have a global language.
我热爱我们有一种全球性语言。

126
00:05:31.820 --> 00:05:34.820
We need one today more than ever.
我们今天比过去任何时候都需要它。

127
00:05:34.820 --> 00:05:36.820
But I am against using it
但是我反对用它

128
00:05:36.820 --> 00:05:38.820
as a barrier.
设立障碍。

129
00:05:38.820 --> 00:05:41.820
Do we really want to end up with 600 languages
我们真的只想留下600种语言

130
00:05:41.820 --> 00:05:44.820
and the main one being English, or Chinese?
而主要语言只是英语和中文吗？

131
00:05:44.820 --> 00:05:47.820
We need more than that. Where do we draw the line?
我们需要更多，我们在哪里划这条界线呢？

132
00:05:47.820 --> 00:05:49.820
This system
这个体制

133
00:05:49.820 --> 00:05:52.820
equates intelligence
把智能

134
00:05:52.820 --> 00:05:55.820
with a knowledge of English,
和英语能力划等号

135
00:05:55.820 --> 00:05:57.820
which is quite arbitrary.
这是非常武断的。

136
00:05:57.820 --> 00:06:03.820
(Applause)
(掌声)

137
00:06:03.820 --> 00:06:05.820
And I want to remind you
我想提醒你

138
00:06:05.820 --> 00:06:08.820
that the giants upon whose shoulders
而当代知识分子所站立在

139
00:06:08.820 --> 00:06:10.820
today's intelligentsia stand
那些“巨人肩膀”上的伟人，

140
00:06:10.820 --> 00:06:12.820
did not have to have English,
他们也并不都具有英语能力，

141
00:06:12.820 --> 00:06:14.820
they didn't have to pass an English test.
他们不需要通过英语考试。

142
00:06:14.820 --> 00:06:17.820
Case in point, Einstein.
爱因斯坦就是个典型。

143
00:06:18.820 --> 00:06:21.820
He, by the way, was considered remedial at school
其实，他在学校的时候是个需要补课的学生

144
00:06:21.820 --> 00:06:23.820
because he was, in fact, dyslexic.
因为他诵读有困难。

145
00:06:23.820 --> 00:06:25.820
But fortunately for the world,
但是也是这世界的幸运，

146
00:06:25.820 --> 00:06:28.820
he did not have to pass an English test.
他不必通过英语考试。

147
00:06:28.820 --> 00:06:31.820
Because they didn't start until 1964
因为1964年

148
00:06:31.820 --> 00:06:33.820
with TOEFL,
托福考试还没设立，

149
00:06:33.820 --> 00:06:35.820
the American test of English.
这是一种美式英语测试。

150
00:06:35.820 --> 00:06:37.820
Now it's exploded.
现在已经泛滥了

151
00:06:37.820 --> 00:06:40.820
There are lots and lots of tests of English.
各种各样的英语测试。

152
00:06:40.820 --> 00:06:42.820
And millions and millions of students
每年成千上万的学生

153
00:06:42.820 --> 00:06:44.820
take these tests every year.
参加这样的考试。

154
00:06:44.820 --> 00:06:46.820
Now you might think, you and me,
你会觉得，你和我都这么认为

155
00:06:46.820 --> 00:06:48.820
"Those fees aren't bad, they're okay,"
这些考试价格还是合理的，

156
00:06:48.820 --> 00:06:50.820
but they are prohibitive
但是数百万穷人

157
00:06:50.820 --> 00:06:52.820
to so many millions of poor people.
却望而却步。

158
00:06:52.820 --> 00:06:54.820
So immediately, we're rejecting them.
所以一开始我们就把他们挡在了外面。

159
00:06:54.820 --> 00:06:57.820
(Applause)
(掌声)

160
00:06:57.820 --> 00:07:00.820
It brings to mind a headline I saw recently:
这让我想到我最近看见的一条新闻：

161
00:07:00.820 --> 00:07:02.820
"Education: The Great Divide."
“教育：大鸿沟。”

162
00:07:02.820 --> 00:07:04.820
Now I get it,
现在我明白了，

163
00:07:04.820 --> 00:07:07.820
I understand why people would want to focus on English.
为什么人们都关注英语。

164
00:07:07.820 --> 00:07:10.820
They want to give their children the best chance in life.
他们希望给予他们的孩子最好的人生机遇。

165
00:07:11.820 --> 00:07:14.820
And to do that, they need a Western education.
而要达到这个目的，他们需要西方教育。

166
00:07:14.820 --> 00:07:16.820
Because, of course, the best jobs
因为，显然，最好的工作

167
00:07:16.820 --> 00:07:19.820
go to people out of the Western Universities,
都让西方大学的毕业生拿走了，

168
00:07:19.820 --> 00:07:21.820
that I put on earlier.
就跟我之前说的一样。

169
00:07:21.820 --> 00:07:23.820
It's a circular thing.
这是个循环。

170
00:07:23.820 --> 00:07:25.820
Okay.
是吧。

171
00:07:25.820 --> 00:07:27.820
Let me tell you a story about two scientists,
让我们告诉你们两个科学家的故事

172
00:07:27.820 --> 00:07:29.820
two English scientists.
有关两个英国科学家。

173
00:07:29.820 --> 00:07:31.820
They were doing an experiment
他们在做一个实验

174
00:07:31.820 --> 00:07:33.820
to do with genetics
跟遗传学有关

175
00:07:33.820 --> 00:07:36.820
and the forelimbs and the hind limbs of animals.
以及研究动物的前后肢，

176
00:07:36.820 --> 00:07:38.820
But they couldn't get the results they wanted.
但是他们无法得到他们想得到的结果。

177
00:07:38.820 --> 00:07:40.820
They really didn't know what to do,
他们有点束手无策，

178
00:07:40.820 --> 00:07:43.820
until along came a German scientist
直到一个德国科学家参与后

179
00:07:43.820 --> 00:07:46.820
who realized that they were using two words
他发现他们在研究前肢和后肢时

180
00:07:46.820 --> 00:07:48.820
for forelimb and hind limb,
用的是两个词，

181
00:07:48.820 --> 00:07:52.820
whereas genetics does not differentiate
而遗传学上并不区分两者

182
00:07:52.820 --> 00:07:54.820
and neither does German.
德语也不区分。

183
00:07:54.820 --> 00:07:56.820
So bingo,
所以瞧儿，

184
00:07:56.820 --> 00:07:58.820
problem solved.
问题解决了。

185
00:07:58.820 --> 00:08:00.820
If you can't think a thought,
如果你想不通

186
00:08:00.820 --> 00:08:03.820
you are stuck.
就卡住了。

187
00:08:03.820 --> 00:08:05.820
But if another language can think that thought,
但是用另外一种语言就可以想通，

188
00:08:05.820 --> 00:08:07.820
then, by cooperating,
那么，通过合作

189
00:08:07.820 --> 00:08:10.820
we can achieve and learn so much more.
我们可以教学相长，受益颇多。

190
00:08:12.820 --> 00:08:14.820
My daughter
我的女儿

191
00:08:14.820 --> 00:08:17.820
came to England from Kuwait.
从科威特回到英国。

192
00:08:17.820 --> 00:08:20.820
She had studied science and mathematics in Arabic.
她已经用阿拉伯语学了科学和数学。

193
00:08:20.820 --> 00:08:23.820
It's an Arabic-medium school.
那是在一所阿拉伯中校。

194
00:08:23.820 --> 00:08:26.820
She had to translate it into English at her grammar school.
在文法学院学习时，她要把所学的内容翻译成英语。

195
00:08:26.820 --> 00:08:28.820
And she was the best in the class
在她们班上，她的这些科目

196
00:08:28.820 --> 00:08:30.820
at those subjects.
是最好的。

197
00:08:30.820 --> 00:08:32.820
Which tells us
这告诉我们

198
00:08:32.820 --> 00:08:34.820
that when students come to us from abroad,
当学生从海外来就读

199
00:08:34.820 --> 00:08:36.820
we may not be giving them enough credit
也许我们没有给他们足够的认可

200
00:08:36.820 --> 00:08:38.820
for what they know,
对于那些他们已经懂得的知识而言

201
00:08:38.820 --> 00:08:41.820
and they know it in their own language.
因为他们已经通过他们的语言掌握了这些知识。

202
00:08:41.820 --> 00:08:43.820
When a language dies,
当语言消失，

203
00:08:43.820 --> 00:08:46.820
we don't know what we lose with that language.
我们不知道我们还失去了什么。

204
00:08:46.820 --> 00:08:50.820
This is -- I don't know if you saw it on CNN recently --
我不知道你们是否看最近的CNN--

205
00:08:50.820 --> 00:08:52.820
they gave the Heroes Award
他们颁发了一枚英雄奖

206
00:08:52.820 --> 00:08:55.820
to a young Kenyan shepherd boy
给一个年轻的肯尼亚牧童，

207
00:08:55.820 --> 00:08:58.820
who couldn't study at night in his village,
在他所住的村庄里，他和其他在村里的孩子一样

208
00:08:58.820 --> 00:09:00.820
like all the village children,
无法在夜晚读书，

209
00:09:00.820 --> 00:09:02.820
because the kerosene lamp,
因为煤油灯烟

210
00:09:02.820 --> 00:09:04.820
it had smoke and it damaged his eyes.
会弄伤他的眼睛。

211
00:09:04.820 --> 00:09:07.820
And anyway, there was never enough kerosene,
而且，他也没有足够的煤油

212
00:09:07.820 --> 00:09:10.820
because what does a dollar a day buy for you?
他们每天只有一美元的收入，能买什么呢？

213
00:09:10.820 --> 00:09:12.820
So he invented
所以他发明了

214
00:09:12.820 --> 00:09:15.820
a cost-free solar lamp.
不需要花钱的太阳能灯。

215
00:09:15.820 --> 00:09:17.820
And now the children in his village
现在他们村里的孩子们

216
00:09:17.820 --> 00:09:19.820
get the same grades at school
都能在学习上取得一样的好成绩

217
00:09:19.820 --> 00:09:23.820
as the children who have electricity at home.
跟那些家里有电的孩子一样。

218
00:09:23.820 --> 00:09:29.820
(Applause)
(掌声)

219
00:09:29.820 --> 00:09:31.820
When he received his award,
当他得到这个奖励时，

220
00:09:31.820 --> 00:09:33.820
he said these lovely words:
他说了这些可爱的话：

221
00:09:33.820 --> 00:09:36.820
"The children can lead Africa from what it is today,
“儿童可以带领今天的非洲

222
00:09:36.820 --> 00:09:38.820
a dark continent,
从一个黑暗的大陆

223
00:09:38.820 --> 00:09:40.820
to a light continent."
走向一个光明的大陆。”

224
00:09:40.820 --> 00:09:42.820
A simple idea,
一个简单的想法

225
00:09:42.820 --> 00:09:45.820
but it could have such far-reaching consequences.
但是其影响是深远的。

226
00:09:46.820 --> 00:09:48.820
People who have no light,
无论是实际生活中还是社会意义上

227
00:09:48.820 --> 00:09:51.820
whether it's physical or metaphorical,
不能享受光明的人

228
00:09:51.820 --> 00:09:54.820
cannot pass our exams,
都无法通过我们的测试，

229
00:09:54.820 --> 00:09:57.820
and we can never know what they know.
我们也无法了解他们拥有的知识。

230
00:09:57.820 --> 00:10:00.820
Let us not keep them and ourselves
我们不能让他们和我们自己都

231
00:10:00.820 --> 00:10:02.820
in the dark.
身处于黑暗里。

232
00:10:02.820 --> 00:10:05.820
Let us celebrate diversity.
让我们一起为多元化欢呼。

233
00:10:05.820 --> 00:10:08.820
Mind your language.
重视你的语言。

234
00:10:08.820 --> 00:10:12.820
Use it to spread great ideas.
用它来传播优秀的思想。

235
00:10:12.820 --> 00:10:19.820
(Applause)
(掌声)

236
00:10:19.820 --> 00:10:21.820
Thank you very much.
非常谢谢。

237
